  "text": "[31] Water/rock ratio (W/R) can be an important influence on the mineralogy of alteration products in hydrothermal systems. Martian hydrothermal alteration is thought to occur at low W/R (<10 by mass) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , in which case its effect is small, and the initial mineral composition is the primary influence on the alteration assemblage [CITATION_3] .",
